[[Malay styles and titles|Datuk]] '''Gabuh bin Piging''' [[Order of Kinabalu|P.G.D.K.]] (11 January 1932 - 31 August 2010) represented [[Crown Colony of North Borneo|North Borneo]] in the [[Athletics at the 1956 Summer Olympics – Men's triple jump|triple jump]] at the [[1956 Summer Olympics]], he finished 24th.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bi/gabuh-bin-piging-1.html Sports-Reference Profile]</ref> He later competed at the [[1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]] in the [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games – Men's long jump|long jump]] and [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games – Men's triple jump|triple jump]] where he finished 10th in the latter.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.adriansprints.com/2010/09/sabahs-first-olympian-datuk-gabuh.html | title=Sabahs first Olympian | publisher=AdrianSprints.com | accessdate=5 April 2015}}</ref>
