{{other uses|Lemhi (disambiguation)}}
{{Book of Mormon}}
In the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Limhi''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|l|ɪ|m|h|aɪ}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «lĭm´hī»</ref> was the third and final king of the second [[Nephite]] habitation of the land of [[Lehi-Nephi]].  He succeeded his father, [[King Noah|Noah]]. Led by [[Ammon (Book of Mormon)|Ammon]], he escaped from the [[Lamanites]] with his people to [[Zarahemla]].

