an02/2002-01-23-eisenberg-kidney.htm Aron 'Nog' Eisenberg beams aboard a kidney.] ''[[USA Today]]'' (January 23, 2002). Retrieved on December 27, 2006.</ref> |- |[[Sean Elliott]] |(1968–) |[[National Basketball Association|NBA]] basketball star. The kidney was donated by his brother. Elliott made history by returning to play in the NBA following his surgery. |August 16, 1999 | |<ref>Falcon, Mike. [https://www.usatoday.com/news/health/spotlight/2002-06-12-elliott-kidney.htm Sean Elliott slam-dunks kidney disease.] ''[[USA Today]]'' (June 12, 2002). Retrieved on December 28, 2006.</ref> |- |[[Selena Gomez]] |(1992–) |Actress and singer. The kidney was donated by Gomez's best friend, actress [[Francia Raisa]]. |2017 | |<ref>{{cite web|last=Respers France|first=Lisa|date=September 15, 2017|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/14/entertainment/selena-gomez-kidney-transplant/index.html|title=Selena Gomez's best friend gave her a kidney this summer|publisher=[[CNN]]|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref> |- |[[Jennifer Harman]] |(1964–) |Poker player; only woman to win two open events in the [[World Series of Poker]]. Had two separate kidney transplants. | | |<ref>[http://www.worldpokertour.com/players/?x=profile&poker-player=2275 Jennifer Harman - Official World Poker Tour Profile.] worldpokertour.com. Retrieved on December 28, 2006.</ref> |- |[[Ken Howard]] | (1932–) |English artist who was president of the [[New English Art Club]] from 1998-2003. |2000 | |<ref>[http://cnnstudentnews.cnn.com/2003/HEALTH/07/11/hln.bio.ken.howard/ CNN news story] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051201113048/http://cnnstudentnews.cnn.com/2003/HEALTH/07/11/hln.bio.ken.howard/ |date=December 1, 2005 }}</ref> |- |[[Ivan Klasnić]] |(1980–) |[[Croatia]]n international [[Association football|footballer]]. After kidney failure in late 2006, he underwent an unsuccessful transplant in January 2007, followed by a successful one from his father two months later. He returned to action with [[Werder Bremen]] in November, and played at [[UEFA Euro 2008|Euro 2008]], becoming the first kidney transplant patient to play in a major football finals. |March 13, 2007 | |<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2008/mar/25/europeanfootball.sport1 | title=Klasnic showing heart after kidney complaint | last=Wilson | first=Jonathan | date=March 25, 2008 | work=[[guardian.co.uk]] | accessdate=2009-12-03 | location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/soccer/klasnic-kidney-transplant-triumph/story-e6frfg8x-1111116656394 | title=Klasnic kidney transplant triumph | agency=[[Reuters]] | date=June 17, 2008 | work=[[Herald Sun]] | accessdate=2009-12-03}}</ref> |- |[[Jimmy Little]] |(1937–2012) |Australian country/rock artist. |February 2004 | |<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/southcoast/stories/s1049865.htm Jimmy Littles' kidney transplant.] ''ABC South Coast WA'' (February 20, 2004). Retrieved on December 27, 2006.</ref> |- |[[Jonah Lomu]] |(1975–2015) |[[New Zealand]] [[All Blacks]] [[rugby union]] player. The kidney was donated by Wellington radio presenter Grant Kereama. Lomu came back to professional rugby in 2005, though not with his past success. | July 28, 2004 | Eleven years |<ref>[http://www.scenta.co.uk/sport/features.cfm?cit_id=21621&FAArea1=customWidgets.content_view_1 Rugby Union: Jonah Lomu interview.] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120908141913/http://www.scenta.co.uk/sport/features.cfm?cit_id=21621&FAArea1=customWidgets.content_view_1 |date=2012-09-08 }} ''[[Guardian Unlimited]]'' (May 30, 2005). Retrieved on December 27, 2006. (</ref> |- |[[George Lopez]] |(1961–) |Actor-Comedian and star of the ''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]'' TV series. Kidney transplant from his wife, Ann Lopez in April 2005 |April 2005 | |<ref>McMillen, Matt. [http://www.webmd.com/content/article/121/114100.htm Perfect Match.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313215051/http://www.webmd.com/content/articl